## 11. Design Checklist

- Every high-priority requirement has a corresponding design item here
- This document explains how, not why
- It does not mix in task lists, schedules, or execution details
- Key risks and trade-offs are explicit
- The stack, architecture direction, and quality goals are explicit
- Any disputed key option includes trade-offs and a clear user-confirmation status
- API naming, error model, database conventions, migration rules, and transaction boundaries are explicit

